 You can trigger this Subflow by passing a message object with thefollowing  float (e.g.  0.1) payload. I recommend using a  Inject Nodeto test this out.
  This flow brings the two previous sub flows together to normalize all volumelevels based on the time of the day. In my home, I set the level to 30% from9:00am to 9:00pm, otherwise I set to 10%.
 To have the flow set the volume levels at different times of the day, I use the BigTimer Nodewith an  On Time of  09:00 and a  Off Time of  21:00. Then I set the ON Msg to  .3 and a  OFF Msg to  .1. When the timer turns on and turns off,it will check to see if my automation flags are turned on. If they are, it willenumerate over all media devices and set the volume based on the timers outputmessage (e.g.,  .1 or  .3).
